'''Mezidimestan Kadın''' (3 March 1869 &ndash; 21 January 1909) was the sixth wife of Sultan [[Abdul Hamid II]] of the [[Ottoman Empire]].{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=248}}

==Early life==
Mezidimestan Kadın was born on 3 March 1869 in [[Gagra]], [[Abkhazia]]. Born as Kadriye Kamile Mikanba, she was a member of Abkhazian noble family Mikanba. Her father was Kaymat Bey Mikanba, and her mother was Princess Feryal Hanım Marshan, an Abkhazian. She was the first cousin of [[Nazikeda Kadın (wife of Mehmed VI)|Nazikeda Kadın]].{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=134}}

In 1876, she had been brought to Istanbul as a young child, where her uncle entrusted her to the imperial harem together with her cousins Emine, Daryal and Naciye, cousins Amine (1872 - 1946), [[Rumeysa Aredba|Rumeysa]] (1875 - 1927), Pakize (1876 - 1943), and Fatima.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=183}}

==Marriage==
Mezidimestan married Abdul Hamid on 2 February 1885 at the Yıldız Palace.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=134}} She was given the title of "Beşinci Kadın". On 19 December 1886, a year after the marriage, she gave birth to her only son, Şehzade Mehmed Burhaneddin.

In 1895, she was given the title of Dördüncü Kadın,{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=248}} and in 1901, she was given the title of Üçüncü Kadın. Abdul Hamid had presented her a villa located on the grounds of Yıldız Palace.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=135}}

Her cousin Daryal renamed Iryale was married to [[Şehzade Mehmed Selim]], son of Sultan [[Abdul Hamid II]].{{sfn|Açba|2004|p=79}}<ref>{{cite book|first=Rumeysa|last=Aredba|first2=Edadil|last2=Açba|title=Sultan Vahdeddin'in San Remo Günleri|publisher=Timaş Yayınları|year=2009|pages=65, 70|isbn=978-9-752-63955-3}}</ref> Her other cousin Amine renamed Nazikeda was married to [[Şehzade Yusuf Izzeddin]], son of Sultan [[Abdülaziz]].{{sfn|Açba|2004|p=82 n. 7}}

==Death==
Mezidimestan died on 21 February 1901 in the Yıldız Palace, and was buried in Yahya Efendi Cemetery, [[Istanbul]].{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=135}}{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=248}}

