'''Romeo Acquarone''' (1895 – 1980) was a professional tennis player born in Monaco <ref>{{cite web|url=http://archives.mairie.mc/ark:/63956/s00572754fb47604/573da956ca1c6|title=Conditions de réutilisation des ressources de ce site - Archives de la ville de Monaco|website=archives.mairie.mc}}</ref>. He became a French citizen in 1937 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k65840886|title=Journal officiel de la République française. Lois et décrets|date=November 28, 1937|publisher=Journaux officiels|via=gallica.bnf.fr}}</ref>. Acquarone won the [[French Pro Championship#Bristol_Cup|Bristol Cup]] in France in 1920 (beating Joseph Negro in the final). The Bristol Cup was the top professional tournament in the world in the 1920s.
